The paper deals with sorting algorithms, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses an evolving data framework, where the algorithm's input data is changing while the algorithm is executing, which is a topic of interest in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the Kendall tau distance, which is a measure of similarity between two rankings and is a topic of interest in information theory (cs.IT) and statistics (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.DS, cs.AI, and cs.LG, followed by cs.IT and cs.SI.
